TASK 1 - WHAT IS THE OSI MODEL?

• OSI = Open Systems Interconnection.
• Standard networking model used to explain how devices communicate.
• Contains 7 layers (Layer 7 → Layer 1).
• Ensures different devices and operating systems can communicate.
• Encapsulation = Process of adding information (headers/trailers) to data as it moves through the layers.

**OSI Layers (Top → Bottom)**
7. Application
6. Presentation
5. Session
4. Transport
3. Network
2. Data Link

1. Physical

